caption.center: COMMONWEALTH of Kentucky, FISH AND WILDLIFE DIVISION, Movant, v. Louis
LANIER and Workmen's Compensation Board, Respondents.

opinion.posture: On review from Court of Appeals, 79-CA-619-MR. (Ballard Circuit Court No. 78-CI-070).
opinion.attorneys:
Jonathan Freed, Boehl, Stopher, Graves Deindoerfer, Paducah, for movant.
Earl T. Osborne, Paducah, for respondent Louis Lanier.
Gerald V. Roberts (as Director), Dept. of Labor, Frankfort, for respondent Workmen's Compensation Bd.
opinion.opinion_text:
OPINION AND ORDER The Court, having considered the briefs of movant and Louis Lanier, and having heard oral argument of movant in this matter, is of the opinion that discretionary review was improvidently granted.
This Court's order granting discretionary review is vacated and the case is remanded to the Court of Appeals for the issuance of its mandate.
All concur.
ENTERED September 2, 1980.
/s/ John S. Palmore Chief Justice
